Description: Fragment of papyrus made up of two misaligned smaller fragments, possibly pieced together for bookbinding purposes. Both fragments bear six lines of a Coptic text written along the fibres (recto) and, on the other side, five lines against the fibres (verso).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380812) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380812)
